# Art Style Guide

## Visual Identity

Insect Wars is set at **insect scale** on natural ground. Everything is organic — no metal, plastic, or man-made materials. A 3 cm pebble is a 3-story boulder. A grass blade is a 20 m tree. Water droplets are lakes.

- **Style:** Semi-stylized / toon — soft gradients, muted earth tones, readable silhouettes
- **Camera:** Top-down RTS, 30–60 m altitude — all art must read from above
- **No glowing/emissive** — use material smoothness and color for distinction
- **Organic only** — no metal, plastic, man-made geometry; all shapes reference real nature

## Scale Reference

| Element | Unity Size | Real-World Equivalent |
|---------|-----------|----------------------|
| Worker ant | ~0.5–0.7 m tall | Small garden ant |
| Mantis fighter | ~0.5 m tall, wider | Praying mantis |
| Bombardier beetle | ~1.0 m tall | Bombardier beetle |
| Hive (nest) | ~7 m (4×2×4 scaled 1.75×) | Ant mound entrance |
| Rotting apple | ~4 m wide, 3 m tall | Fallen garden apple |
| Pebble (scatter) | 0.3–1.1 m | Garden gravel stone |
| Grass blade (scatter) | 1.2–3.2 m tall | Single grass blade |

## Color Palette

### Team Colors (`TeamPalette`)

| Role | Player | Enemy |
|------|--------|-------|
| **Shell / skin** | Light blue `(0.3, 0.65, 1.0)` | Warm orange-red `(1.0, 0.35, 0.2)` |
| **Accent / straps** | Vibrant blue `(0.0, 0.45, 1.0)` | Vibrant red `(1.0, 0.05, 0.0)` |
| **Weapon accent** | Blue `(0.2, 0.5, 1.0)` | Red `(1.0, 0.2, 0.2)` |

Team colors are applied as a **two-tone system**: the **shell color** (lighter, skin-like) covers the main body, and the **accent color** (vibrant, saturated) marks **straps, rings, and shoulder pads** that act as team identifiers — like military insignia on insects.

